---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Me" description="Learn more about Emma Lane - Senior Software Engineer & Team Lead">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center">About Me</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row mt-4">
      <div class="col text-center">
        <p>Hello! I'm Emma Lane, a Senior Software Engineer and Team Lead with over 12 years of experience in software engineering across multiple technologies, projects, and domains. I thrive in start-up and scale-up environments, bringing strong technical expertise and leadership to every project.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Welcome to Spark Lane, my digital garden where I share my journey through code, leadership, and continuous learning.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-1">
        <div class="row mt-4">
          <div class="border border-gray-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h2>Beyond Code</h2>
            <p>When I'm not coding, you'll find me exploring creative pursuits, experimenting in the kitchen, or diving into gaming worlds. I believe that diverse interests fuel creativity and bring fresh perspectives to technical problem-solving.</p>
            <p>Whether it's debugging a complex issue, perfecting a recipe, or strategizing in a game, I approach everything with curiosity, persistence, and a desire to learn and improve.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <!-- Right Column - Tab Navigation and Content -->
        <div class="about-me-container">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <nav class="flex space-x-8" aria-label="Tabs">
              <button 
                onclick="showTab('philosophy')" 
                id="philosophy-btn"
                class="tab-btn active border-b-2 py-2 px-1 text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out hover:opacity-80 cursor-pointer"

              >
                Approach & Philosophy
              </button>
              <button 
                onclick="showTab('space')" 
                id="space-btn"
                class="tab-btn border-b-2 border-transparent py-2 px-1 text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out hover:opacity-80 cursor-pointer"
             >
                This Space
              </button>
              <button 
                onclick="showTab('technical')" 
                id="technical-btn"
                class="tab-btn border-b-2 border-transparent py-2 px-1 text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out hover:opacity-80 cursor-pointer"
              >
                Technical Expertise
              </button>
              <button 
                onclick="showTab('experience')" 
                id="experience-btn"
                class="tab-btn border-b-2 border-transparent py-2 px-1 text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out hover:opacity-80 cursor-pointer"
              >
                Professional Experience
              </button>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Tab Content -->
        <div class="mt-8">
          <!-- Approach & Philosophy Tab -->
          <div id="philosophy-content" class="tab-content">
            <p>
              I believe in writing clean, maintainable code and creating user experiences that are both functional and delightful. I approach development with an emphasis on accessibility first, continuous learning, community engagement, and user-centred design. By prioritising these principles, I aim to build inclusive experiences that work for everyone, foster a culture of continuous improvement, and contribute to the advancement of the tech industry as a whole.
            </p> 
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Accessibility First</strong>: Building inclusive experiences that work for everyone</li>
              <li><strong>Continuous Learning</strong>: Staying curious and embracing new technologies</li>
              <li><strong>Community Engagement</strong>: Contributing to open source and sharing knowledge</li>
              <li><strong>User-Centred Design</strong>: Putting people at the heart of technical decisions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <!-- This Space Tab -->
          <div id="space-content" class="tab-content hidden">
            <p>Spark Lane is where I document my professional journey, share technical insights, and explore creative pursuits. Here you'll find:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Blog Posts</strong>: Technical tutorials, development insights, and industry thoughts; as well as more personal and ethical musings</li>
              <li><strong>Portfolio</strong>: Projects showcasing my skills, problem-solving approach, and creative pursuits</li>
              <li><strong>Recipes</strong>: A creative outlet sharing favorite dishes and any culinary experiments</li>
              <li><strong>Gaming</strong>: Personal guides, resources and references for games, combining technical analysis with gaming passion</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Technical Expertise Tab -->
          <div id="technical-content" class="tab-content hidden">
            <p>I work with a diverse and modern tech stack, CI/CD and with a deep expertise in a multitude of technologies:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Backend</strong>: C#, .NET & .NET Core, ASP.NET, NodeJS, NestJS, Python, Java</li>
              <li><strong>Frontend</strong>: React, VueJS, NextJS, AngularJS, TypeScript as well as various CSS frameworks</li>
              <li><strong>CMS</strong>: Umbraco, Wordpress, Contentful</li>
              <li><strong>Databases</strong>: MS SQL, MySQL, PostgreSQL, NoSQL (12 years of SQL experience)</li>              
              <li><strong>Cloud & DevOps</strong>: Azure DevOps, Azure Web Apps, Azure Functions, Docker</li>
              <li><strong>Testing</strong>: Jest, Cypress, Selenium, Playwright</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Professional Experience Tab -->
          <div id="experience-content" class="tab-content hidden">
            <p>With extensive experience across the entire software lifecycle, I've successfully designed, developed and deployed numerous desktop and web-based applications while working with and managing mixed-discipline teams. </p>
            <p>My career spans from junior development to team leadership, with key roles including: Team Lead, Senior Software Engineer and Lead Back-end Developer.</p>
            <p>Throughout my career, I have worked across multiple industries, from fintech to digital agencies to defense, and have delivered projects of varying sizes and complexity while developing strong leadership and technical expertise.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <script is:inline>
      function showTab(tabName) {
        // Hide all content immediately
        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content').forEach(content => {
          content.classList.add('hidden');
          content.classList.remove('tab-fade-in');
        });
        
        // Remove active class from all buttons
        document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(btn => {
          btn.classList.remove('active');
        });
        
        // Show selected content with fade animation
        const selectedContent = document.getElementById(tabName + '-content');
        selectedContent.classList.remove('hidden');
        selectedContent.classList.add('tab-fade-in');
        
        // Add active class to clicked button
        const activeBtn = document.getElementById(tabName + '-btn');
        activeBtn.classList.add('active');
        
        // Reset scale after animation
        setTimeout(() => {
          activeBtn.style.transform = 'scale(1)';
        }, 200);
      }
    </script>

      <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h2>Let's Connect!</h2>
          <p>I'm always excited to connect with my peers. Whether you're interested in collaboration, have a project in mind, or want to discuss leadership and technical challenges, I'd love to hear from you!</p>
          <p>Feel free to reach out through <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/emmalouiselane/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a> or email me at <a href="mailto:emma@sparklane.dev">emma@sparklane.dev</a>!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
